The Citizens of the World Festival, which opened in 2012, is a continuation of a global anti-poverty project led by an international group of human rights defenders hoping to end poverty by increasing the number of people actively fighting it.
To get a free ticket to the event (if you’re not ready to pay for a VIP ticket), you’d have to volunteer or email a world leader, make a phone call, or take any other or other meaningful action to help raise awareness of your goal.
